# Backend Development Rules

## 🚀 Node.js/Express Backend Guidelines

### **Server Configuration**
- **Main Server**: [backend/server.js](mdc:backend/server.js) - Express app with security middleware
- **Port**: Default 5000, configurable via `PORT` environment variable
- **Environment**: Development/Production modes with appropriate configurations

### **API Structure**
- **Base URL**: `/api` prefix for all routes
- **Authentication**: JWT-based with refresh tokens
- **Rate Limiting**: 100 requests/15min (production), 1000 requests/15min (development)
- **CORS**: Configured for mobile apps and web clients

### **Route Organization**
- **Auth Routes**: [backend/routes/auth.js](mdc:backend/routes/auth.js) - Login, register, OAuth
- **User Routes**: [backend/routes/users.js](mdc:backend/routes/users.js) - Profile management
- **Resume Routes**: [backend/routes/resumes.js](mdc:backend/routes/resumes.js) - CRUD operations
- **Template Routes**: [backend/routes/templates.js](mdc:backend/routes/templates.js) - Template management
- **Subscription Routes**: [backend/routes/subscriptions.js](mdc:backend/routes/subscriptions.js) - Payment plans
- **Upload Routes**: [backend/routes/uploads.js](mdc:backend/routes/uploads.js) - File handling
- **AI Routes**: [backend/routes/ai.js](mdc:backend/routes/ai.js) - AI-powered features

### **Database Models**
- **User Model**: [backend/models/User.js](mdc:backend/models/User.js) - User authentication and profile
- **Resume Model**: [backend/models/Resume.js](mdc:backend/models/Resume.js) - Resume data structure
- **Template Model**: [backend/models/Template.js](mdc:backend/models/Template.js) - Template definitions
- **Subscription Model**: [backend/models/Subscription.js](mdc:backend/models/Subscription.js) - Payment plans
- **Contact Model**: [backend/models/Contact.js](mdc:backend/models/Contact.js) - Contact form submissions

### **Security Implementation**
- **Authentication**: [backend/middleware/auth.js](mdc:backend/middleware/auth.js) - JWT protection
- **XSS Protection**: Custom sanitization for resume content with CKEditor support
- **MongoDB Injection**: `express-mongo-sanitize` middleware
- **Rate Limiting**: `express-rate-limit` with OAuth exclusions
- **CORS**: Configured for mobile and web clients

### **AI Integration**
- **Gemini Service**: [backend/services/geminiservice.js](mdc:backend/services/geminiservice.js) - Google AI integration
- **Document Parser**: [backend/utils/documentParser.js](mdc:backend/utils/documentParser.js) - PDF/Word parsing
- **Token System**: [backend/utils/tokenCalculator.js](mdc:backend/utils/tokenCalculator.js) - AI usage tracking

### **File Handling**
- **Uploads**: [backend/routes/uploads.js](mdc:backend/routes/uploads.js) - Profile pictures and documents
- **Static Files**: Thumbnails and uploads served with proper caching
- **Document Processing**: PDF and Word document parsing with AI

### **Payment Integration**
- **Razorpay**: [backend/routes/payment.js](mdc:backend/routes/payment.js) - Payment processing
- **Subscription Plans**: Free, Pro Monthly, Pro Yearly with trial periods
- **Token System**: AI action usage tracking and limits

### **Development Scripts**
- **Build Scripts**: [backend/scripts/](mdc:backend/scripts/) - Build and deployment utilities
- **Template Management**: Template seeding and thumbnail generation
- **Database Utilities**: User management and data migration scripts

### **Error Handling**
- **Global Handler**: [backend/middleware/errorHandler.js](mdc:backend/middleware/errorHandler.js)
- **Logging**: Winston logger with file and console output
- **Graceful Shutdown**: MongoDB connection cleanup

### **Environment Variables**
```env
# Required
JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/resumebuilder
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Optional
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=oauth-client-id
RAZORPAY_SECRET_KEY=payment-secret
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=cloud-storage
```

### **API Response Format**
```javascript
// Success Response
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { /* response data */ }
}

// Error Response
{
  "success": false,
  "error": "Error message"
}
```

### **Testing and Development**
- **Health Check**: `GET /health` - Server status endpoint
- **Development**: `npm run dev` with nodemon
- **Production**: `npm start` with proper error handling
- **Database**: MongoDB with Mongoose ODM